{"title_page": "Gr\u00e9goire Margotton", "text_new": "{{short description|French sports journalist}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates| date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox presenter\n| name             = Gr\u00e9goire Margotton\n| image            = File:Gr\u00e9goire Margotton.jpg\n| image_upright    = \n| caption          = Gr\u00e9goire Margotton commentating in 2017\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1969|11|9|df=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[Lyon]], France\n| alma_mater       = \n| show             = [[T\u00e9l\u00e9foot]]\n| network          = {{flatlist|* [[Canal+]]\n* [[TF1]]}} \n| country          = France\n}}\n\n'''Gr\u00e9goire Margotton''' (born 9 November 1969)<ref name=Liberation/> is a French [[sports journalist]] who has worked for French television channels [[Canal+]] and [[TF1]]. Since 2018, he has been the main presenter of the TF1 football programme [[T\u00e9l\u00e9foot]].\n\n==Personal life==\nMargotton's father taught at [[Lumi\u00e8re University Lyon 2]].<ref name=Liberation>{{cite news| url= https://www.liberation.fr/sports/2016/05/29/gregoire-margotton-euro-d-etre-la_1455927| title= Gr\u00e9goire Margotton, Euro d\u2019\u00eatre l\u00e0| language=fr| last=Lefilli\u00e2tre| first=J\u00e9r\u00f4me| work=[[Lib\u00e9ration]]| date=29 May 2016| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> He studied his [[Baccalaur\u00e9at]] in [[Lyon]], before moving to Liverpool, England as an [[Erasmus programme|Erasmus student]].<ref name=Liberation/>\n\n==Career==\nMargotton studied journalism at Bietry school, which was named after French journalist {{ill|Charles Bietry|fr}}.<ref name=Liberation/> In 1992, he started working for [[Canal+]] as an intern.<ref name=Liberation/> Margotten and [[Darren Tulett]] were the French language commentators on the ''[[Pro Evolution Soccer 2013]]'' game.<ref>{{cite web| url= https://www.jeuxactu.com/pes-2013-les-commentateurs-83132.htm| title= PES 2013 : DAREN TULLET ET GR\u00c9GOIRE MARGOTTON PARLENT DU JEU| language=fr| publisher=Jeux Actu| date=14 September 2012| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> In 2014, Margotten started presenting ''La Data Room de Canal +'' (''The Canal+ data room''), a weekly short programme that looks into the statistics of football matches.<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.mediasportif.fr/2014/09/15/canal-lance-sa-data-room/| title= Canal + Lance Sa Data Room| language=fr| work=Media Sportif| date=15 September 2014| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> In the same year, Margotten suggested that matches between [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] and [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] should become a [[derby match]].<ref>{{cite news| url= https://blog.lefigaro.fr/football/bruno_roger-petit/2014/03/psg-om-ne-lappelons-plus-clasico-mais-derby-de-france.html| title= PSG-OM, ne l'appelons plus \"Clasico\", mais \"Derby de France\"...| language=fr| last=Roger-Petit| first=Bruno| work=[[Le Figaro]]| date=2 March 2014| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Margotton moved from Canal+ to [[TF1]], as he wanted to spend his weekends with his family rather than at football matches.<ref name=Liberation/>{{efn|Since 2007, rights to [[Ligue 1]] football were held by Canal+. T\u00e9l\u00e9foot shows highlights of foreign matches, European club competitions, and international matches.<ref name=Obs>{{cite news| url= https://www.nouvelobs.com/sport/20120106.OBS8266/telefoot-c-etait-mieux-avant-au-temps-de-thierry-roland.html| title= \"T\u00e9l\u00e9foot\", c'\u00e9tait mieux avant, au temps de Thierry Roland| language=fr| last=Kefi| first=Ramses|work=[[L'Obs]]| date=6 January 2012| accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal| url= http://gymnasium.ub.ro/index.php/journal/article/download/506/690| title=The French Ligue 1 TV Rights Selling Model \u2013 Historical Study| last=Koutroumanides| first=Christos|journal=Scientific Journal of Education, Sports, and Health|publisher=[[University of Bac\u0103u]]| volume=19| date=2018| accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref>}} His first match for TF1 was the T\u00e9l\u00e9foot coverage of an international friendly between [[France national football team|France]] and [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]].<ref name=Liberation/> He was chosen ahead of [[Christian Jeanpierre]] to present T\u00e9l\u00e9foot's coverage of France matches at [[UEFA Euro 2016]], and commentated alongside [[Bixente Lizarazu]].<ref name=Monde>{{cite news| url= https://www.lemonde.fr/actualite-medias/article/2016/05/10/tf1-chipe-gregoire-margotton-a-canal_4916636_3236.html| title= TF1 chipe Gr\u00e9goire Margotton \u00e0 Canal+| language=fr| last=Delcambre| first=Alexis| work=[[Le Monde]]| date=10 May 2016| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.huffingtonpost.fr/2016/03/29/christian-jeanpierre-tf1-remplace-gregoire-margotton-euro-2016_n_9562612.html| title= Christian Jeanpierre remplac\u00e9 par Gr\u00e9goire Margotton sur TF1 \u00e0 partir l'Euro 2016, selon L'\u00c9quipe| work=[[HuffPost]]| date=29 March 2016| accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref> In September 2017, Margotton began hosting ''Rendez-vous Sport'', a two-minute summary programme about football results and players.<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.mediasportif.fr/2017/09/09/tf1-et-france-2-lancent-des-pastilles-sportives-apres-leurs-journaux/| title= TF1 et France 2 lancent des pastilles sportives apr\u00e8s leurs journaux| last=Messant| first=Nicholas| work=MediaSportif| date=9 September 2017| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> Prior to the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]], Margotten and {{ill|Nicolas Glimois|fr}} hosted a documentary ''98, secrets d'une victoire'' (''98, secrets of a victory'') about France's victory at the [[1998 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.lci.fr/culture/98-secrets-d-une-victoire-gregoire-margotton-et-nicolas-glimois-reviennent-sur-le-triomphe-des-bleus-2089986.html| title= \"98, secrets d'une victoire\" : Gr\u00e9goire Margotton et Nicolas Glimois reviennent sur le triomphe des Bleus| language=fr| work=[[La Cha\u00eene Info]]| date=8 June 2018| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> After the 2018 World Cup, Margotten replaced Jeanpierre as the main presenter of T\u00e9l\u00e9foot.<ref>{{cite news| url= https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/telefoot-gregoire-margotton-succedera-a-christian-jeanpierre-1441136.html| title= T\u00e9l\u00e9foot: Gr\u00e9goire Margotten Succ\u00e9dera \u00c0 Christian Jeanpierre| language=fr| work=[[BFM TV]]| date=9 March 2018| accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=Orange>{{cite news| url=https://orangefootballclub.com/fr/articles/medias-christian-jeanpierre-quittera-telefoot-en-fin-de-saison/| title= M\u00e9dias : Christian Jeanpierre quittera T\u00e9l\u00e9foot en fin de saison| language=fr| work=Media365| via=[[Orange S.A.]]| date=28 April 2018| accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref> Margotten and Lizarazu commentated for the T\u00e9l\u00e9foot coverage of the [[2019 FIFA Women's World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.lequipe.fr/Medias/Actualites/Coupe-du-monde-2019-tf1-presente-son-dispositif/1016290| title= Coupe du monde 2019 : TF1 pr\u00e9sente son dispositif| language=fr| work=[[L'\u00c9quipe]]| date=7 May 2019| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nAside from football, Margotton has commentated for TF1 on [[handball]]. He commentated on the [[2017 World Men's Handball Championship|2017 Men's]]<ref name=Figaro>{{cite news| url= https://tvmag.lefigaro.fr/programme-tv/gregoire-margotton-se-lance-dans-le-handball_edd5a5ba-e18a-11e6-9abe-50d11d5e9b14/| title= Gr\u00e9goire Margotton se lance dans le handball| language=fr| last=Barenghi| first=Jean-Marc| work=[[Le Figaro]]| date=24 January 2017| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> and [[2017 World Women's Handball Championship|Women's World Handball Championship]]s,<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.ozap.com/actu/handball-feminin-le-quart-de-finale-france-montenegro-sur-tmc-demain-soir/544897| title=Handball f\u00e9minin : Le quart de finale France/Mont\u00e9n\u00e9gro sur TMC demain soir| language=fr| work=[[Ozap]]| date=11 December 2017| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> the 2018 [[Women's EHF Champions League]],<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.lequipe.fr/Medias/Actualites/La-finale-de-la-ligue-des-champions-de-handball-diffusee-en-clair-sur-tfx/897732| title= La finale de la Ligue des champions de handball diffus\u00e9e en clair sur TFX| language=fr| work=[[L'\u00c9quipe]]| date=2 May 2018| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> and the [[2019 World Men's Handball Championship]].<ref>{{cite news| url= https://tvmag.lefigaro.fr/programme-tv/mondial-de-hand-les-experts-sur-tmc_a1dd536a-1b17-11e9-833a-06cc65142907/| title=Mondial de Hand : les Experts sur TMClanguage=fr| last=Barenghi| first=Jean-Marc| work=[[Le Figaro]]| date=19 January 2019| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Margotton appeared on a special edition of ''[[Qui veut gagner des millions ?]]'' to raise money for [[Notre-Dame de Paris]]\nfollowing the [[Notre-Dame de Paris fire|fire there]]. Margotten and [[Alessandra Sublet]] won 24,000[[Euro|\u20ac]].<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.telestar.fr/actu-tv/qvgdm/qui-veut-gagner-des-millions-arthur-donne-28-000-a-la-fondation-du-patrimoine-po-422232| title= Qui veut gagner des millions : Arthur donne 28 000 euros \u00e0 la Fondation du Patrimoine pour atteindre les 100 000 euros| language=fr| work=Telestar| date=19 April 2019| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\nIn 2013, Margotton was awarded the ''Lucarnes d'Or'' award for best French sports journalist.<ref name=Monde/><ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.programme.tv/news/actu/52200-lucarnes-dor-gregoire-margotton-meilleur-commentateur-de-foot/| title= Lucarnes d'or : Gr\u00e9goire Margotton, meilleur commentateur de foot| language=fr| last=Robert| first=Thomas| work=Programme.tv| date=11 May 2013| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> In 2017, he was voted the French public's favourite commentator in a [[French Football Federation]] poll.<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.lequipe.fr/Medias/Actualites/Gregoire-margotton-est-le-commentateur-prefere-des-francais/810044| title=Gr\u00e9goire Margotton est le commentateur pr\u00e9f\u00e9r\u00e9 des Fran\u00e7ais| language=fr| work=[[L'\u00c9quipe]]| date=13 June 2017| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:French sports journalists]]\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Lyon]]\n[[Category:French television presenters]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|French sports journalist}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates| date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox presenter\n| name             = Gr\u00e9goire Margotton\n| image            = File:Gr\u00e9goire Margotton.jpg\n| image_upright    = \n| caption          = Gr\u00e9goire Margotton commentating in 2017\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1969|11|9|df=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[Lyon]], France\n| alma_mater       = \n| show             = [[T\u00e9l\u00e9foot]]\n| network          = {{flatlist|* [[Canal+]]\n* [[TF1]]}} \n| country          = France\n}}\n\n'''Gr\u00e9goire Margotton''' (born 9 November 1969)<ref name=Liberation/> is a French [[sports journalist]] who has worked for French television channels [[Canal+]] and [[TF1]]. Since 2018, he has been the main presenter of the TF1 football programme [[T\u00e9l\u00e9foot]].\n\n==Personal life==\nMargotton's father taught at [[Lumi\u00e8re University Lyon 2]].<ref name=Liberation>{{cite news| url= https://www.liberation.fr/sports/2016/05/29/gregoire-margotton-euro-d-etre-la_1455927| title= Gr\u00e9goire Margotton, Euro d\u2019\u00eatre l\u00e0| language=fr| last=Lefilli\u00e2tre| first=J\u00e9r\u00f4me| work=[[Lib\u00e9ration]]| date=29 May 2016| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> He studied his [[Baccalaur\u00e9at]] in [[Lyon]], before moving to Liverpool, England as an [[Erasmus programme|Erasmus student]].<ref name=Liberation/>\n\n==Career==\nMargotton studied journalism at Bietry school, which was named after French journalist {{ill|Charles Bietry|fr}}.<ref name=Liberation/> In 1992, he started working for [[Canal+]] as an intern.<ref name=Liberation/> Margotten and [[Darren Tulett]] were the French language commentators on the ''[[Pro Evolution Soccer 2013]]'' game.<ref>{{cite web| url= https://www.jeuxactu.com/pes-2013-les-commentateurs-83132.htm| title= PES 2013 : DAREN TULLET ET GR\u00c9GOIRE MARGOTTON PARLENT DU JEU| language=fr| publisher=Jeux Actu| date=14 September 2012| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> In 2014, Margotten started presenting ''La Data Room de Canal +'' (''The Canal+ data room''), a weekly short programme that looks into the statistics of football matches.<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.mediasportif.fr/2014/09/15/canal-lance-sa-data-room/| title= Canal + Lance Sa Data Room| language=fr| work=Media Sportif| date=15 September 2014| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> In the same year, Margotten suggested that matches between [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] and [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] should become a [[derby match]].<ref>{{cite news| url= https://blog.lefigaro.fr/football/bruno_roger-petit/2014/03/psg-om-ne-lappelons-plus-clasico-mais-derby-de-france.html| title= PSG-OM, ne l'appelons plus \"Clasico\", mais \"Derby de France\"...| language=fr| last=Roger-Petit| first=Bruno| work=[[Le Figaro]]| date=2 March 2014| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Margotton moved from Canal+ to [[TF1]], as he wanted to spend his weekends with his family rather than at football matches.<ref name=Liberation/>{{efn|Since 2007, rights to [[Ligue 1]] football were held by Canal+. T\u00e9l\u00e9foot shows highlights of foreign matches, European club competitions, and international matches.<ref name=Obs>{{cite news| url= https://www.nouvelobs.com/sport/20120106.OBS8266/telefoot-c-etait-mieux-avant-au-temps-de-thierry-roland.html| title= \"T\u00e9l\u00e9foot\", c'\u00e9tait mieux avant, au temps de Thierry Roland| language=fr| last=Kefi| first=Ramses|work=[[L'Obs]]| date=6 January 2012| accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal| url= http://gymnasium.ub.ro/index.php/journal/article/download/506/690| title=The French Ligue 1 TV Rights Selling Model \u2013 Historical Study| last=Koutroumanides| first=Christos|journal=Scientific Journal of Education, Sports, and Health|publisher=[[University of Bac\u0103u]]| volume=19| date=2018| accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref>}} His first match for TF1 was the T\u00e9l\u00e9foot coverage of an international friendly between [[France national football team|France]] and [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]].<ref name=Liberation/> He was chosen ahead of [[Christian Jeanpierre]] to present T\u00e9l\u00e9foot's coverage of France matches at [[UEFA Euro 2016]], and commentated alongside [[Bixente Lizarazu]].<ref name=Monde>{{cite news| url= https://www.lemonde.fr/actualite-medias/article/2016/05/10/tf1-chipe-gregoire-margotton-a-canal_4916636_3236.html| title= TF1 chipe Gr\u00e9goire Margotton \u00e0 Canal+| language=fr| last=Delcambre| first=Alexis| work=[[Le Monde]]| date=10 May 2016| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.huffingtonpost.fr/2016/03/29/christian-jeanpierre-tf1-remplace-gregoire-margotton-euro-2016_n_9562612.html| title= Christian Jeanpierre remplac\u00e9 par Gr\u00e9goire Margotton sur TF1 \u00e0 partir l'Euro 2016, selon L'\u00c9quipe| work=[[HuffPost]]| date=29 March 2016| accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref> In September 2017, Margotton began hosting ''Rendez-vous Sport'', a two-minute summary programme about football results and players.<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.mediasportif.fr/2017/09/09/tf1-et-france-2-lancent-des-pastilles-sportives-apres-leurs-journaux/| title= TF1 et France 2 lancent des pastilles sportives apr\u00e8s leurs journaux| last=Messant| first=Nicholas| work=MediaSportif| date=9 September 2017| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> Prior to the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]], Margotten and {{ill|Nicolas Glimois|fr}} hosted a documentary ''98, secrets d'une victoire'' (''98, secrets of a victory'') about France's victory at the [[1998 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.lci.fr/culture/98-secrets-d-une-victoire-gregoire-margotton-et-nicolas-glimois-reviennent-sur-le-triomphe-des-bleus-2089986.html| title= \"98, secrets d'une victoire\" : Gr\u00e9goire Margotton et Nicolas Glimois reviennent sur le triomphe des Bleus| language=fr| work=[[La Cha\u00eene Info]]| date=8 June 2018| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> After the 2018 World Cup, Margotten replaced Jeanpierre as the main presenter of T\u00e9l\u00e9foot.<ref>{{cite news| url= https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/telefoot-gregoire-margotton-succedera-a-christian-jeanpierre-1441136.html| title= T\u00e9l\u00e9foot: Gr\u00e9goire Margotten Succ\u00e9dera \u00c0 Christian Jeanpierre| language=fr| work=[[BFM TV]]| date=9 March 2018| accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=Orange>{{cite news| url=https://orangefootballclub.com/fr/articles/medias-christian-jeanpierre-quittera-telefoot-en-fin-de-saison/| title= M\u00e9dias : Christian Jeanpierre quittera T\u00e9l\u00e9foot en fin de saison| language=fr| work=Media365| via=[[Orange S.A.]]| date=28 April 2018| accessdate=19 April 2020}}</ref> Margotten and Lizarazu commentated for the T\u00e9l\u00e9foot coverage of the [[2019 FIFA Women's World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.lequipe.fr/Medias/Actualites/Coupe-du-monde-2019-tf1-presente-son-dispositif/1016290| title= Coupe du monde 2019 : TF1 pr\u00e9sente son dispositif| language=fr| work=[[L'\u00c9quipe]]| date=7 May 2019| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nAside from football, Margotton has commentated for TF1 on [[handball]]. He commentated on the [[2017 World Men's Handball Championship|2017 Men's]]<ref name=Figaro>{{cite news| url= https://tvmag.lefigaro.fr/programme-tv/gregoire-margotton-se-lance-dans-le-handball_edd5a5ba-e18a-11e6-9abe-50d11d5e9b14/| title= Gr\u00e9goire Margotton se lance dans le handball| language=fr| last=Barenghi| first=Jean-Marc| work=[[Le Figaro]]| date=24 January 2017| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> and [[2017 World Women's Handball Championship|Women's World Handball Championship]]s,<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.ozap.com/actu/handball-feminin-le-quart-de-finale-france-montenegro-sur-tmc-demain-soir/544897| title=Handball f\u00e9minin : Le quart de finale France/Mont\u00e9n\u00e9gro sur TMC demain soir| language=fr| work=[[Ozap]]| date=11 December 2017| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> the 2018 [[Women's EHF Champions League]],<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.lequipe.fr/Medias/Actualites/La-finale-de-la-ligue-des-champions-de-handball-diffusee-en-clair-sur-tfx/897732| title= La finale de la Ligue des champions de handball diffus\u00e9e en clair sur TFX| language=fr| work=[[L'\u00c9quipe]]| date=2 May 2018| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> and the [[2019 World Men's Handball Championship]].<ref>{{cite news| url= https://tvmag.lefigaro.fr/programme-tv/mondial-de-hand-les-experts-sur-tmc_a1dd536a-1b17-11e9-833a-06cc65142907/| title=Mondial de Hand : les Experts sur TMClanguage=fr| last=Barenghi| first=Jean-Marc| work=[[Le Figaro]]| date=19 January 2019| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Margotton appeared on a special edition of ''[[Qui veut gagner des millions]]'' to raise money for [[Notre-Dame de Paris]]\nfollowing the [[Notre-Dame de Paris fire|fire there]]. Margotten and [[Alessandra Sublet]] won 24,000[[Euro|\u20ac]].<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.telestar.fr/actu-tv/qvgdm/qui-veut-gagner-des-millions-arthur-donne-28-000-a-la-fondation-du-patrimoine-po-422232| title= Qui veut gagner des millions : Arthur donne 28 000 euros \u00e0 la Fondation du Patrimoine pour atteindre les 100 000 euros| language=fr| work=Telestar| date=19 April 2019| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\nIn 2013, Margotton was awarded the ''Lucarnes d'Or'' award for best French sports journalist.<ref name=Monde/><ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.programme.tv/news/actu/52200-lucarnes-dor-gregoire-margotton-meilleur-commentateur-de-foot/| title= Lucarnes d'or : Gr\u00e9goire Margotton, meilleur commentateur de foot| language=fr| last=Robert| first=Thomas| work=Programme.tv| date=11 May 2013| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> In 2017, he was voted the French public's favourite commentator in a [[French Football Federation]] poll.<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.lequipe.fr/Medias/Actualites/Gregoire-margotton-est-le-commentateur-prefere-des-francais/810044| title=Gr\u00e9goire Margotton est le commentateur pr\u00e9f\u00e9r\u00e9 des Fran\u00e7ais| language=fr| work=[[L'\u00c9quipe]]| date=13 June 2017| accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:French sports journalists]]\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Lyon]]\n[[Category:French television presenters]]\n", "name_user": "Joseph2302", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCareer:link fix", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gr%C3%A9goire_Margotton"}
